  <sec sec-type="conclusions" id="sec013">
    <title>Discussion</title>
    <p>In the following sections we address some remaining discussion points and suggest ways to improve SoilGrids and embark on new research directions. Although we have reached current effective limits imposed by software capabilities and availability of remote sensing data sources, the accuracy of SoilGrids could still be improved. Globally, by adding more covariates based on the most recent remote sensing data (see <xref ref-type="fig" rid="pone.0169748.g011">Fig 11</xref>), and locally, by combining global predictions with local prediction models. Global models could be further improved especially by revising (even re-designing) each of the three main components of the system:</p>
    <list list-type="bullet">
      <list-item>
        <p>Soil training data,</p>
      </list-item>
      <list-item>
        <p>Statistical / Machine Learning models, and</p>
      </list-item>
      <list-item>
        <p>Covariate layers.</p>
      </list-item>
    </list>
